pullRequest.title: Pass RemoteTable to createTableSql
pullRequest.bodyText:
Pass RemoteTable to createTableSql
Passing RemoteTable is much less error prone that passing a triple of
Strings. Especially, where some of them are nullable.

/**

However, then I am not sure whether @JsonProperty adds anything. Maybe it's totally redundant?
is it? the code looks like it's not

Maybe add TODO in the body, to remove special treatment for "" values.
(isNullOrEmpty => != null)

final
(this module is intended to be extended by external parties, so we should be more paranoid the eg in presto-main)

commit.message:
Pass RemoteTable to createTableSql

Passing RemoteTable is much less error prone that passing a triple of
Strings. Especially, where some of them are nullable.
